duck: Self-archiving - Self-archiving is one of two general methods for providing open access.
Cryptology ePrint Archive - The Cryptology ePrint Archive is an electronic archive of new results in the field of cryptography, maintained by the International Association for Cryptologic Research.
preprint definition: an issue of a technical paper often in preliminary form before its publication in a journal.
ScientificCommons - ScientificCommons is a project of the University of St. Gallen Institute for Media and Communications Management.
In academic publishing, a preprint is a draft of a scientific paper that has not yet been published in a peer-reviewed scientific journal.
Prepress - Prepress is the term used in the printing and publishing industries for the processes and procedures that occur between the creation of a print layout and the final printing.
